{{Infobox prepared food | name = Bryndzové halušky | image = Bryndzové halušky so slaninou.jpg | image_size = 250px | caption = Bryndzové Halušky with bacon | alternate_name = | country = [[Slovakia]] | region = | creator = | course = | type = [[Dumpling]] | served = | main_ingredient = [[Halušky]], [[bryndza]] | variations = | calories = | other = }} '''''Bryndzové Halušky''''' (English: '''potato dumplings with sheep cheese'''<ref>{{cite book|last1=Gottfried|first1=Ted|title=Slovakia|date=2005|publisher=Marshall Cavendish|page=130|accessdate=20 September 2017}}</ref>) is one of the [[national dish]]es in [[Slovakia]].<ref name=cravens2006p75>{{cite book |first=Craig Stephen |last=Cravens |title=Culture and customs of the Czech Republic and Slovakia |publisher=[[Greenwood Publishing Group]] |location=[[Westport, Connecticut]] |year=2006 |page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=kDYjlpeoxiMC&pg=PA75 75]|isbn=0-313-33412-9 |oclc=67240291 }}<!--|accessdate=1 March 2009--></ref><ref name=dunford2007p452>{{cite book |first=Lisa |last=Dunford |chapter=Slovakia: Food & Drink |chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=gIymIi4UvFcC&pg=PA452 |editor=Paul Smitz |editor2=Aaron Anderson |editor3=Steve Kokker |editor4=Brett Atkinson |editor5=Becca Blond |title=Lonely Planet Central Europe |publisher=[[Lonely Planet]] |location=[[Hawthorn, Victoria]] |year=2007 |page=452 |isbn=1-74104-301-8 |oclc=85763619 }}</ref> This hearty meal consists of [[halušky]]<ref name=sinkovec2004>{{cite book |first=Magdalena |last=Sinkovec |chapter=Bryndzové Halušky / Potato Dumplings with 'Bryndza' Sheep Cheese and Bacon |chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=9fNgBO3aEK8C&pg=PA115 |title=Culinary Cosmic Top Secrets A Nato Cookbook |year=2004 |publisher=[[Lulu (company)|Lulu]] |pages=115–16 |isbn=1-4116-0837-2 }}</ref> (boiled lumps of potato dough similar in appearance to [[gnocchi]]<ref name=sinkovec2004/><ref name=cravens2006p75/><ref name=dunford2007p452/>) and [[bryndza]]<ref name=sinkovec2004/> (a soft sheep cheese<ref name=cheese.com>{{cite web |url=http://www.cheese.com/Description.asp?Name=Bryndza |title=Cheese Description: Bryndza |accessdate=1 March 2009 |publisher=Cheese.com }}</ref>), optionally sprinkled with cooked bits of smoked pork fat/bacon.<ref name=sinkovec2004/><ref name=cravens2006p75/><ref name=dunford2007p452/>
[[Žinčica]] is traditionally drunk with this meal.<ref name=cravens2006p75/> There is an annual Bryndzové Halušky festival in [[Turecká]] that features an [[Competitive eating|eating contest]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.spectator.sk/articles/view/4209/9/ |title=Three liters of bryndzové halušky small work for hefty men in national eating competition |first=Matt |last=Reynolds |accessdate=1 March 2009 |work=[[The Slovak Spectator]] |date=21 June 1999}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.haluskyturecka.sk/ |title=Halušky Turecká |language=Slovak |year=2008 |accessdate=1 March 2009 |publisher=Občianske združenie Halušky Terchová |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090227010612/http://haluskyturecka.sk/ |archivedate=27 February 2009 |df= }}</ref>
